17/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The High Court in Belgrade will rule in the trial of ultranationalist group Obraz leader Mladen Obradovic and 13 other people on April 20th.
Both the prosecutors and the defence delivered final arguments on Friday.
Obradovic and members of his group are charged with orchestrating protests during Belgrade's Gay Pride Parade last October.
More than 140 people were injured during clashes with demonstrators.
If convicted, the Obraz leader faces up to 12 years in prison.
(Tanjug, Beta - 15/04/11)
